This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques for detecting negation and uncertainty in radiology reports. It also utilizes patterns on universal dependencies, which is a common technique in NLP. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the proposed algorithm, NegBio, is a machine learning-based approach. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper deals with information extraction from radiology reports. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the proposed algorithm involves NLP and machine learning techniques, which are common in AI research. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as the paper deals with the impact of technology on healthcare and medical practices.
